params.name: token_ids
params.description: List of tokenized input ids. Can be obtained using the __call__ method.

params.name: skip_special_tokens
params.description: Whether or not to remove special tokens in the decoding.

params.name: clean_up_tokenization_spaces
params.description: Whether or not to clean up the tokenization spaces.

params.name: output_char_offsets
params.description: Whether or not to output character offsets. Character offsets can be used in combination with thesampling rate and model downsampling rate to compute the time-stamps of transcribed characters.Please take a look at the Example of ~models.wav2vec2.tokenization_wav2vec2.decode to betterunderstand how to make use of output_word_offsets.~model.wav2vec2_phoneme.tokenization_wav2vec2_phoneme.batch_decode works the same way withphonemes.

params.name: kwargs
params.description: Will be passed to the underlying model specific decode method.
